      "content": "I understand your discomfort, but ibuprofen is not a good choice for you with chronic kidney disease. Instead, try taking a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) like acetaminophen, but be sure to limit the dose to 3,000 mg per day. Also, make sure you drink plenty of water to stay hydrated. If the headache persists, you should definitely consult a healthcare professional.",
